The paper deals with the complexity and expressivity of propositional dynamic logics, which are typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the semantic expressiveness of variable-free fragments, which is related to the study of formal languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
